{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"064c6c84-bea8-4baa-9c08-737351598c53","content":"Here's the correct skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four report the reason in test results so you can track why tests were skipped. The skipped tests won't count as passed or failed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a123b0b5-6bf3-41ef-b1d6-4921f0f4a6eb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about skip/ignore attributes across MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a straightforward knowledge question about test framework APIs. I can answer this directly without needing to look up anything.","outputTokens":221,"requestId":"5C20:C4D03:19BD9D:203022:69F54ECB"},"id":"0623842f-a9f3-441c-b1a2-0e1ed36b6fd5","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:09:37.612Z","parentId":"c6e5c855-9941-4e7c-bdc2-ff82768a2c7a"}
